cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MA, cs.GT

This paper deals with the performance analysis of a multi-tier cellular communication network, which involves the study of wireless communication, network information theory, stochastic geometry, and game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the analysis of outage probabilities, which falls under the category of information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of stochastic geometry to model the locations of users and access points, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category. The paper also involves the use of game theory to model the open access policy, making cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the performance bounds, making cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) a possible category as well.
